garage.model

Class TicketSystem

  • java.lang.Object
    • garage.model.TicketSystem
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public final class TicketSystem
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    The TicketSystem class stores and handles the opening and closing of tickets. There can only be one instance of a TicketSystem object at any given point once instantiated. The object can be accessed once imported using the getInstance() method.
    Version:
    1.0 Dec. 17, 2017.
    Author:
    Feng Parra
    See Also:

      • openTicket

        public void openTicket(java.lang.String firstName,
                       java.lang.String lastName,
                       java.lang.String licensePlate,
                       java.lang.String phoneNum)
        Creates a new ticket using the customers information. A new Customer object is created and stored within the Ticket object. An open space is retrieved then assigned with the customers vehicle. The ticket is then saved in the openTickets Map.
        Parameters:
        firstName - Customers first name.
        lastName - Customers last name.
        licensePlate - Vehicles license plate number associated with the customer.
        phoneNum - Customers primary contact number.

      • closeTicket

        public void closeTicket(java.lang.String key)
        Closes a ticket based on the tickets ID number. Departure is determined along with the payment amount then passed to the closedTickets Stack. The space assigned to the customers vehicle is pulled and placed back in its appropriate Queue.
        Parameters:
        key - The ticket numbers ID.
